trans-unit.source: Defines an interface that can be implemented in a type in order to preload the type in an ASP.NET application that is running on [!INCLUDE[iisver](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)].
This interface is intended primarily for use by WCF applications that are non-HTTP applications.

ASP.NET developers who want to preload ASP.NET Web applications should use the simulated HTTP requests in [!INCLUDE[iisver](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] combined with the `Application_Start` method in the Global.asax file.

> [!NOTE] > The IProcessHostPreloadClient type and its methods apply only to applications that run on [!INCLUDE[iisver](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] and [!INCLUDE[win7](~/add/includes/win7-md.md)].
Provides initialization data that is required in order to preload the application.
The value of `parameters` can be `null`, a zero-length array, or a populated array.

> [!NOTE] > The <xref:System.Web.Hosting.IProcessHostPreloadClient> type and its methods apply only to applications that run on [!INCLUDE[iisver](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] and [!INCLUDE[win7](~/add/includes/win7-md.md)].
This parameter can be <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref> or an empty array.
